**Guys pls help me.** I describe my approach for ur better underatanding...   
**Approach:**  

in construtor: 
Store the words in a hashmap, "key = words[i], value: 0(not necessary)" and store words length in a treemap, "key = words[i].length, value: 0(not necessary)". 

In qyery :
	traverse the treemap 
			get the substring of that length from end.
			check in hashmap if there is any key present. if present return true.
	after traverse if there is no such suffix return False.

```
class StreamChecker {
	HashMap <String, Integer> hashmap = new HashMap<> ();
	TreeMap <Integer, Integer> treemap = new TreeMap<> ();

	String stream = "";

	int maxLen, minLen;
	public StreamChecker(String[] words) {
		for(String S: words) {
			treemap.put(S.length(), 0);
			hashmap.put(S, S.length());
		}

		maxLen = treemap.lastKey();
		minLen = treemap.firstKey();
	}

	public boolean query(char letter) {
		stream += String.valueOf(letter);

		if(stream.length() < minLen) return false;

		if(stream.length() > maxLen) stream = stream.substring(1);
    	// System.out.println("stream: "+stream+"\tletter: "+letter);

		for(Map.Entry len : treemap.entrySet()) {
			int loc = stream.length() - (int)len.getKey();
			if(loc >= 0) {
				String temp = stream.substring(loc);

				if(hashmap.containsKey(temp)) return true;

			}
		}
		return false;
	}
}
```

