Make a trie and insert all the words in order.
Make a waiting list, which will store all the potential answers. As soon as the potenial dissappers (not forming a word), delete that node from the waiting list.
And always check if from root, we can go to a next node, depending upon the query letter.

Consider the trie with the words: ab, ba, aaab, abab, baa

<img src="https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/2eedfb3f-e881-49e3-a3fc-ef51a59886ca_1598248043.5687332.png" width=30%>

Note: The 'X' is the root, and the small 'x' marked beside the node, means theres a word ending there

Let the queries be: a,a,a,a,a,b,a,b,a,b
The content in the waiting list will be: (The number before the character is its corresponding number in the trie. See the diagram)

a              ```[2a]``` False
a              ```[4a. 2a]``` False
a              ```[7a, 4a, 2a]``` False
a              ```[7a, 4a, 2a]``` False (the previous 7a got deleted, 4a moved to 7a, 2a moved to 4a and 2a added from the root)
a              ```[7a, 4a, 2a]``` False (same as above)
b              ```[10b, 5b, 3b]``` (7a moved to 10b, 4a was deleted as there's no next b, 2a moved to 5b and 3b was added from root). Answer: True, as 10b and 5b both end on a word. Similarly follow the next steps:
a              ```[8a, 6a, 2a]``` True, 6a ends on a word
b              ```[11b, 5b, 3b]``` True, 11b and 5b end on a word
a              ```[8a, 6a, 2a]``` True, 6a ends on a word
b              ```[11b, 5b, 3b]``` True, 11b and 5b end on a word

In the waiting list, if any node was a word written in it, we set the answer to be true ans return ans.
So final result: F, F, F, F, F, T, T, T, T, T
