**Intuition:**
Used hashset to store the words and look for it. We have to maintain a window of size of the word with max length. So once the size of the StringBuilder exceeds that length, we pop a char at the front. So essentially, sb acts as a queue here.
So the time complexity of 1 query is O(maxlength(words))
```
class StreamChecker {
    HashSet<String> dict = new HashSet<>();
    int window = 0;
    StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
    public StreamChecker(String[] words) {
        for(String word :  words) {
            dict.add(word);
            window = Math.max(window, word.length());
        }

    }

    public boolean query(char letter) {
        sb.append(letter);
        if(sb.length() > window)
            sb.deleteCharAt(0);
        for(int i=0; i<sb.length();i++){
            if(dict.contains(sb.substring(i)))
                return true;
        }
        return false;
    }
}
