Query characters from the latest to previous, should match a word from the last character to the first (if any). So it would be more convenient if we reverse the word and perform the matching.

In this way, query characters from the latest to previos seem like a prefix of a reversed word. A prefix tree (trie) is a good storage of these reversed wrods.

Only latest maxLen query characters matter, so we clear the staled characters after each query().
```
    private Node root;
    private int maxLen;
    private StringBuilder queries;

    public StreamChecker(String[] words) {
        root = new Node();
        maxLen = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        queries = new StringBuilder();

        for (String word : words) {
            // reverse word insert into trie
            insert(new StringBuilder(word).reverse().toString());
            // update maxLen
            maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, word.length());
        }
    }

    // Clear stale before return
    public boolean query(char letter) {
        queries.append(letter);
        Node node = root;

        for (int i = queries.length() - 1; i >= Math.max(0, queries.length() - maxLen); i--) {
            // search queries character by character from end in trie
            node = node.children[queries.charAt(i) - 'a'];
            if (node == null) {
                clearStale();
                return false;
            } else if (node.isLeaf) {
                clearStale();
                return true;
            }
        }

        clearStale();
        return false;
    }

    private void insert(String s) {
        Node ptr = root;
        for (char ch : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (ptr.children[ch - 'a'] == null) {
                ptr.children[ch - 'a'] = new Node();
            }
            ptr = ptr.children[ch - 'a'];
        }
        ptr.isLeaf = true;
    }

    class Node {
        Node[] children;
        boolean isLeaf;

        public Node() {
            children = new Node[26];
            isLeaf = false;
        }
    }

    // only maxLen query characters need to be maintained
    // so we clear the staled characters after each query (adding a new character)
    private void clearStale() {
        if (queries.length() >= maxLen) {
            queries.deleteCharAt(0);
        }
    }
```

